12/11/2007
DETROIT, United States -- A Serb man was arrested by US immigration officers while entering the United States from Canada on Friday (November 9th), plice reported. Goran Pavic, 42, was on an Interpol list of suspects wanted for committing war crimes in Croatia. He moved to Canada a decade ago and worked as a long-haul trucker. Croatian prosecutors say he was a member of a Serb militia that terrorised residents of the village of Sotin, in eastern Croatia, as part of a wider ethnic cleansing campaign in late 1991 and early 1992. (AFP, Canadian Press - 11/11/07) 
